The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | SMS Meer sets up shop in Calcutta
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       SMS Meer sets up shop in Calcutta
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 19: Germanys SMS Meer, which manufactures equipment for the steel industry, has set up a base in Calcutta.        
	SMS Meer India, the wholly owned subsidiary, will supply rolling mills, to make long products such as bars and rods, to various steel mills coming up in eastern India.        
	It will also take up turnkey contracts, providing design and engineering for the mills it set up.        
	Announcing the launch of its Indian arm, Bimal K Sarkar, CEO and managing director of the company, said the city was chosen as the base to be close to the market and customers.        
	The company, at present, supplies equipment to a 800,000-tonne structural mill coming up at IISCO Steel Plant in Burnpur, Bengal.        
	It is also eyeing contracts in various private steel projects in eastern India.        
	Apart from steel, SMS Meer India will also participate in the installation and commissioning of plants for non-ferrous metals.        
	Apart from India, SMS Meer has wholly owned subsidiaries in Austria, Italy, the US and China.                                                                                                                                     
